#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pre-requisites
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"confFlu" is a "common configuration package" for the "pythonFlu" related
developement. For it's operation it requires "GNU automake" tools (tested with 1.9.6 and
1.10.2) to be installed in your environment.


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installation
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The installation procedure for the "confFlu" consists of the following simple steps
(it is not necessary to compile anything):

1. Start a new shell session to ensure a clear environment.

2. Go to the source directory:

   cd <path to the sources>

3. Launch configure procidures:

   ./build_configure
   ./configure

   Make sure that after each configuration step the "--- OK ---" message is
   printed in your console.

4. Install confFlu:  
   
   sudo make install

#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"confFlu" installation check
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A file "build_configure" should appear in the /usr/local/share/confFlu


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"confFlu" utility environment
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To use "confFlu" functionality, include "/usr/local/share/confFlu/build_configure" launching in your "build_configure" script


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

